## Problem Space

(Unchanged from PROPOSAL-1)

**Axes:**
- **Scale:** 110 providers, 4,168 models (up from 3 providers, 110 models)
- **Identity:** Models have dual identity — provider-scoped (Provider, Family, Variant, Date) AND cross-provider (Family, Variant, Date)
- **Stability:** Provider slugs are stable. Model IDs have high churn.
- **Has-a:** A Provider HAS many Models. A Model HAS one canonical identity (ModelRef). Multiple provider-scoped Models may share the same cross-provider identity.
- **Is-a:** A ModelRef IS a 3-field decomposition of a ModelInfo. Provider constants ARE generated from API data (except ProviderLocal).

## Engineering Tradeoffs

| Decision | Options | Chosen | Rationale |
|----------|---------|--------|-----------|
| Provider constant ownership | Hand-written vs generated | Generated (providers_gen.go) | 110 providers can't be hand-maintained. aws-sdk-go-v2 precedent. |
| ProviderLocal | Generated vs hand-written | Hand-written (stays in provider.go) | Bestiary-specific concept, not from API. |
| knownProviders location | init() composition vs fully generated | Fully generated in providers_gen.go | Simpler, no cross-file init() (Reviewer C feedback). Codegen knows about ProviderLocal. |
| Model data default | All providers vs curated | All 110 providers (~3.8MB source) | User chose "all providers" as default. |
| ModelRef fields | 5-field (with empty Family/Variant) vs 3-field | 3-field (Provider, RawFamily, Date) | Family/Variant are empty until normalization epoch. Simpler MVP. (Reviewer C feedback) |
| Cross-provider query | New ModelsByRawFamily() vs existing ModelsByFamily() | Reuse ModelsByFamily() | Identical behavior. New function was dead duplication. (Reviewers A + C feedback) |
| Filter flags | -providers + -exclude-providers | Same, with mutual exclusivity error | Specifying both is a hard error. (Reviewers A + C feedback) |
| Filter asymmetry | Constants filtered vs always generated | Constants always generated; only model DATA is filtered | Provider constants are lightweight (~5KB). Users should always have typed access to all providers even if they don't ship all model data. Filter controls binary size, not type safety. |
| IsKnown() semantics | Original 4 only vs all API providers | All API providers + ProviderLocal | User chose coordinated release with provenance. |
| Test strategy | Exact counts vs property-based | Property-based + regression guards | Property tests for invariants, lower-bound count for regression. (Reviewer B feedback) |
| Schema version | 0.0.2 vs 0.1.0 | 0.1.0 | New public type (ModelRef). Semver minor bump. (Reviewer A confirmed) |

