### Modified: provider.go

```go
package bestiary

import "fmt"

// Provider identifies the organization that hosts or publishes an AI model.
type Provider string

// ProviderLocal is a bestiary-specific provider for locally-hosted models.
// It is not derived from the models.dev API and is always included in
// knownProviders (generated in providers_gen.go).
const ProviderLocal Provider = "local"

// IsKnown reports whether p is a recognized Provider (any API provider or ProviderLocal).
// The known set is generated from the models.dev API at codegen time.
func (p Provider) IsKnown() bool {
    for _, known := range knownProviders {
        if p == known {
            return true
        }
    }
    return false
}

// Providers returns all known Provider values. The returned slice is a
// defensive copy — modifying it does not affect the package state.
func Providers() []Provider {
    out := make([]Provider, len(knownProviders))
    copy(out, knownProviders[:])
    return out
}

// String, MarshalText, UnmarshalText — unchanged.
```

### New: modelref.go

```go
package bestiary

// ModelRef represents the canonical identity of a model as a 3-tuple.
// It captures the provider-scoped identity using the raw API family field.
//
// Future epochs will decompose RawFamily into separate Family and Variant
// fields via a normalization pipeline. For now, RawFamily is the API's
// "family" field verbatim (e.g., "claude-opus", "gemini-flash-lite").
type ModelRef struct {
    Provider  Provider // Hosting provider
    RawFamily string   // API family field verbatim (e.g., "claude-opus")
    Date      string   // Release date, if present (from ModelInfo.ReleaseDate)
}

// Ref returns a ModelRef for this ModelInfo.
// RawFamily is the API family field. Date is the ReleaseDate field.
func (m ModelInfo) Ref() ModelRef {
    return ModelRef{
        Provider:  m.Provider,
        RawFamily: m.Family,
        Date:      m.ReleaseDate,
    }
}

// ProvidersForFamily returns the set of providers that host models with
// the given family string. Useful for answering "who hosts claude-opus?"
// The family parameter matches the raw API family field.
func ProvidersForFamily(family string) []Provider {
    seen := make(map[Provider]struct{})
    var out []Provider
    for _, m := range staticModels {
        if m.Family == family {
            if _, ok := seen[m.Provider]; !ok {
                seen[m.Provider] = struct{}{}
                out = append(out, m.Provider)
            }
        }
    }
    return out
}
```

Note: `ModelsByFamily()` in `registry.go` already provides the cross-provider query. No new `ModelsByRawFamily()` function is needed.

